data.text:
Ole Miss' Lane Kiffin hires brother, Chris, as an analyst

Mississippi coach Lane Kiffin, who, with the sixth-ranked Rebels, will open the season Saturday against Furman, has hired his brother, Chris, as a player personnel analyst, marking the fourth time the brothers have worked together.

Dabo Swinney radio show only taking text questions from fans

Clemson coach Dabo Swinney's weekly radio show is no longer taking calls, instead asking listeners to text in their questions.

Sarkisian reestablishing Texas football's personality

Steve Sarkisian says he's confident the Longhorns have what it takes to compete with the best in their first year in the SEC, even with new faces.

OU's Venables aims to control the game amidst CFB changes

Brent Venables dives into the rule changes and trends he is monitoring as Oklahoma looks to keep moving in the right direction and battle Temple in Week One.

DeBoer and Tide excited to battle WKU

Kalen DeBoer says Alabama is confident in its preparation and doesn't expect to miss a beat against Western Kentucky in his Tide coaching debut.
